spans.text: not that Day in circling Moments run , When first these Eyes beheld the odious Sun
descend in baneful Showers , And horrid Darkness mix the jumbling Hours
Let his gay Beams forsake the mourning Fields , And starting backward roll his flaming Wheels
trembling Mortals gaze in vain for Light , Cursed be the Day
Let sulphurous Hail descend in baneful Showers , And horrid Darkness mix the jumbling Hours
pale-eyed Spectres burst their yawning Tombs
I in her tender Bosom grow , A fostered Subject of impending Woe
Where frozen Pride and conquered Vengeance lies
their Wants supplied , Thrice happy Rest
returning Morn : The piercing Sun thrusts in a spiteful Ray , To wound my Eyelids with unwelcome Day
a spiteful Ray , To wound my Eyelids with unwelcome Day
Tyrannic Death , whom trembling Mortals flee , The Prince of Ills to every Wretch but me , Plays with the Torments of my struggling Heart , And over
at my Heels pursue a meagre Train Of pining Sickness and distorting Pain , Pale-eyed Confusion with dishiveled Hair , And wild Impatience leading on Despair
I with Crimes profane my Days of Rest
Crimes profane my Days of Rest
guilty Flame my tainted Soul surprise
If ever Oppression stained my guiltless Hands
my God his flaming Vengeance throw
If ever Oppression stained my guiltless Hands
every Good obeyed my lordly Will
I by Fraud increase the tempting Store
painted Idols , or the beaming Sun
